  "claim_short": "Conditional reduction for Cuth-Raunig Question 3 asking whether aa_p^1(2)>1 for every p in (0,1). Assuming the isolated Scalar Lemma E for Euclidean tripods, the packet proves aa_{1/2}^1(2)=1, which would be a negative answer to the universal question. Local and web novelty checks found no existing answer to the sharp two-point q=1 constant; arXiv:2603.28193 answers the broad canonical embedding question but not...",
